## summon

### Instructions


You have these skills at your disposal, when it is clear they can help you solve a problem or you are asked to use them:
• ai-compact - Suggests manual context compaction at logical intervals to preserve context through task phases rather than arbitrary auto-compaction.
• ai-eval - Evaluation framework for Claude Code sessions, implementing eval-driven development (EDD) principles
• ai-learning - Automatically extract reusable patterns from Claude Code sessions and save them as learned skills for future use.
• ai-skills - Expert guide for creating, maintaining, and managing Claude Code skills in the ~/.claude/skills/ directory
• ai-verify - Comprehensive verification system for Claude Code sessions
• aia-jack - Enterprise Software Organization Analysis - Expert in analyzing and summarizing enterprise software research for Chinese manufacturing companies (MES, WMS, hanging systems)
• aia-k8s - Expert guide for Kubernetes cluster setup on Ubuntu, including single-node clusters, CNI configuration (Cilium), proxy setup, deploying services like npm registry with persistent storage, dynamic user creation via npm adduser, HTTPRoute configuration for Envoy Gateway with HTTPS support, SSL/TLS wildcard certificate setup with certbot, and comprehensive troubleshooting for kernel modules, swap issues, and networking problems.
• aia-k8sicp - Expert guide for ICP2 Kubernetes infrastructure management, including PostgreSQL database setup with proper user privileges, Redis cache deployment, OpenTelemetry Collector configuration, and Gateway API routing. Covers database user creation, privilege granting (database + schema public), and connection methods.
• aia-k8sspeak - Deploy whisperx-asr-service and speakr to Kubernetes with GPU support
• aia-ops - Expert Linux system administration operations for Ubuntu/Kubuntu systems including display manager configuration, plymouth boot themes, package management, alternatives system troubleshooting, ELF binary/executable stack fixes, and fcitx5 input method for Electron apps on Wayland.
• aia-pm - Expert project management using Eisenhower Matrix MCP tools for task tracking, daily reporting, and project organization across multiple work streams.
• aidev-backend - Backend architecture patterns, API design, database optimization, and server-side best practices for Node.js, Express, and Next.js API routes.
• aidev-bash - Advanced bash scripting patterns for tool development with subcommands, JSON manipulation, and clean argument handling
• aidev-coding - Universal coding standards, best practices, and patterns for TypeScript, JavaScript, React, and Node.js development.
• aidev-crossplatform - Cross-platform application development using Flutter, Dart, Android, Java, and native platforms
• aidev-frontend - Frontend development patterns for React, Next.js, state management, performance optimization, and UI best practices.
• aidev-gimp - Expert knowledge for developing and maintaining the embedded MCP (Model Context Protocol) server in GIMP 3.0, including Go-based MCP server integration, build system configuration, tool implementation, and troubleshooting.
• aidev-go - Expert Go module development with DDD architecture, supporting both applications and libraries
• aidev-goapp - Expert Go GraphQL application development using gqlgen framework, with DDD architecture, custom scalars, manual VOs, and service layer integration
• aidev-golib - Expert guide for developing production-ready Go libraries (not applications) for open-source distribution
• aidev-guidelines - Example project-specific skill template for Claude Code
• aidev-java - Java开发规范指南，涵盖编程规范、数据库设计、缓存、搜索引擎和业务安全最佳实践
• aidev-libreoffice - Expert guide for developing and maintaining the iLibreOffice extension
• aidev-py - Reusable patterns for building production-ready Python CLI applications
• aidev-tdd - Use this skill when writing new features, fixing bugs, or refactoring code. Enforces test-driven development with 80%+ coverage including unit, integration, and E2E tests.
• aigc-gimp - Expert creative art guidance for generating eye-catching images using GIMP tools via MCP - including icons, logos, text-on-background designs, and visual compositions
• aigc-impress - Build professional LibreOffice Impress presentations using MCP tools with optimized layouts, no overlaps, and clean formatting.
• aigc-impress-basic - Build clean, modern LibreOffice Impress presentations using the template-shape-basic style with optimized layouts, minimal design, and professional formatting.
• aigc-wechat - Expert guide for creating and publishing WeChat public account articles - from codebase analysis to formatted content with cover images. Includes reliable clipboard-based transfer for large articles (2000+ words).
• aiops-clickhouse - ClickHouse database patterns, query optimization, analytics, and data engineering best practices for high-performance analytical workloads.
• aisec-security - Use this skill when adding authentication, handling user input, working with secrets, creating API endpoints, or implementing payment/sensitive features. Provides comprehensive security checklist and patterns.
• leaf-doc-guide - Reference leaf documentation to create, configure, or explain leaf-specific features like recipes, extensions, sessions, and providers. You MUST fetch relevant leaf docs before answering. You MUST NOT rely on training data or assumptions for any leaf-specific fields, values, names, syntax, or commands.
